        Precision in financing is the difference between a profitable build and a terminal funding gap.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-12">
      <p>
        Financing a major construction project is a complex balancing act where time and money are inextricably linked. The loan maze involves more than just securing an interest rate. It requires a precise understanding of how funds are disbursed and how that timing affects the total cost of capital. Professional builders know that a construction loan estimator is only as good as the data driving the underlying draw schedule.
      </p>
      
      <figure class="my-12">
        <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1704742950992-9815a104820c?crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&ixid=M3w4NTU2MDF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxjb25zdHJ1Y3Rpb24lMjBzaXRlJTIwaG91c2UlMjBidWlsZGluZ3xlbnwwfHx8fDE3NzQ1NDU2Mjl8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&q=80&w=1080" alt="Active construction site with wooden framing" class="rounded-2xl shadow-xl border border-gray-100">
        <figcaption class="text-sm text-center text-gray-500 mt-4 italic">
          Photo by <a href="https://unsplash.com/@taylorheeryphoto" class="underline hover:text-primary">Taylor Heery</a> on Unsplash
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
